1 (d) Two (2) commissioners shall be appointed in the following manner:
2 1. By the chief executive officer of the county or city, if the commission
3 has been established by separate action of a county or city; or
4 2. One (1) each by the chief executive officer of the county and by the
5 chief executive officer of the most populous city participating in the
6 establishment of the commission, if the commission has been
7 established by joint action of a county and a city or cities.
8 (2) A candidate submitted for appointment to the commission, pursuant to subsection
9 (1)(a) to (1)(c) of this section, shall be appointed by the appropriate chief executive
10 officer or officers within thirty (30) days of the receipt of the required list or lists.
11 Vacancies shall be filled in the same manner that original appointments are made.
12 (3) The commissioners shall be appointed for terms of three (3) years, provided, that in
13 making the initial appointments, the appropriate chief executive officer or officers
14 shall appoint two (2) commissioners for a term of three (3) years, two (2)
15 commissioners for a term of two (2) years and three (3) commissioners for a term of
16 one (1) year. There shall be no limitation on the number of terms to which a
17 commissioner is reappointed. Subsequent appointments shall be for three (3) year
18 terms.
19 (4) The commission shall elect from its membership a chair[chairman] and a treasurer,
20 and may employ personnel and make contracts necessary to carry out the purpose
21 of KRS 91A.345 to 91A.394. The contracts may include, but shall not be limited to,
22 the procurement of promotional services, advertising services, and other services
23 and materials relating to the promotion of tourist and convention business.
24 Contracts of the type enumerated shall be made only with persons, organizations,
25 and firms with experience and qualifications for providing promotional services and
26 materials, such as advertising firms, chambers of commerce, publishers, and
27 printers.
